{
  "texts": [
    "In the visual analytics, particularly in the temporal sequence of published works, terms such as \"drawing,\" \"diagram,\" \"calculation,\" \"technology-based learning,\" \"research,\" \"open system,\" \"mathematics,\" \"objects,\" \"technology acceptance model,\" \"mathematical software,\" and \"open-source software,\" which appeared between 2007 and 2015, reflect the fundamental application of GeoGebra software during that period.",
    "This vocabulary underscores the software's inherent modularity and its relevant application across various mathematical disciplines.",
    "For instance, Velichová (2011) asserted that GeoGebra facilitates the production of self-contained dynamic worksheets and could be utilized in e-learning as a dynamic and interactive platform for calculations and drawings.",
    "It integrates dynamic geometry, algebraic expressions, graphs, and spreadsheets into a unified environment (Hanc et al., 2011).",
    "GeoGebra's effectiveness in teaching complex functions was further validated in subsequent studies, demonstrating its capacity to foster deductive reasoning and mathematical discussions (Breda & Dos Santos, 2016; d'Azevedo Breda & Dos Santos, 2021)."
  ]
}